perPostData.comment:
"After settling into the Moloch Chalet, we set out on our first adventure, a quick tour to an ice cave in the glacier. 
Upon arrival, we popped off our skis and splitboards and slid into the cave on or butts through a small, dark hole in the snow. I gathered myself at the bottom, dusted off some snow and looked up in utter amazement at the scene around me. 
Striations of blue and white like a sandstone slot canyon unfold all around me. Light dashes in and bounces around the cathedral of ice.‚Ä® Ive seen images of ice caves and massive ice structures before, but this experience was unparalleled to what you see in photos.‚Ä® We all instantly returned to a childhood state of wonder and playfulness, sliding and climbing and running our hands along the walls of the cave.

The sad truth is that we are only able to access this cave because the glacier is receding. Ruedi explained that after hundreds of thousands of years of forming, the glacier had receded the distance we covered on our skins--a mile or so--in just a decade. 
This sticks with me the rest of the trip. Every-time I looked down at the glacier, it was clear to see where it once was.‚Äù #revelstoke #marmot #wereouthere #likeachild #wild #protectpubliclands @selkirkmtnexperience 
Photos: @mason_mashon

"On our tour the day before, Ruedi has pointed out the ladder climbing up the rock walls across the valley from the hut. That‚Äôs where we go tomorrow,¬ù is about all he said about it. It was slightly ominous, but I was stoked. 
We skinned across, strapped our skis to our backs, and made our way up the ladders after Ruedi furiously dug out a platform of snow at the base of the ladders for us to stage. 
The ladders were epic! What a sick experience! I‚Äôm a climber and I‚Äôm a skier, but rarely do I combine the two like this. No ropes, or backup of any kind, just a firm grip and big clunky ski boots. Every little slip I reminded myself of the severity of the consequences. It was mildly unsettling, but nothing I wouldn‚Äôt do again.‚Ä®
Topping out on to secure ground was fantastic. Not only because of the security, but we now had a full view of the terrain we‚Äôd be skiing." - @liamjmcnally

#revelstoke #marmot #bornwild #wereoutthere

Don't hit the snooze button! Never miss a chance to feel the warmth of sunrise on the mountains. Alpine starts are worth every minute of sleep missed. It's time for adventure. 
#wereoutthere #marmot #ski #sunrise

Happy New Year to all!! As we turn the page into a new decade, we reflect on the jaw dropping adventures that ensued and the bonds formed over the last year. We'd love to know....what challenged you the most? What inspired you? What humbled you? It's time to reset our clocks, be grateful for the opportunities that came a-knocking last year and point to the new horizon.

May your fires burn brighter, may your horizon stretch farther, may your stories remain plentiful, may your friendships and bonds continue to enrich and may you forever be a marmot...the most social and mountain thirsty species on the planet. 
#wearemarmot #newyear #2020 #marmot #bornwild

‚ÄúWe as people have something in common. The yearning for adventure. However, it is nerve racking to go into the backcountry with people you don‚Äôt know. Communication is key. There is no weakness in admitting fear. It makes you stronger in your discipline to learn from those who know more and to practice humility.‚Äù @meredithdrangin

Learn, practice, communicate, practice safety, execute, repeat.

#humbleyourself #wereouthere #marmot #communication #mountainlife #revelstoke

Photos: @mason_mashon

The sun was just creeping in. We needed to move fast to get to the goods before the sun did. Ruedi sets a pace like nobody I‚Äôve ever toured or hiked with. The man is a machine! I was shedding layers like my life depended on it. 
The day is clearer than yesterday and as we climb, the vastness and density of the Selkirk becomes more and more apparent. Truly stunning. Endless peaks in every direction. We skied a few laps in the area directly above the ladders, chasing the sections with the least sun exposure. Ruedi, Meredith, and I took a few runs side-by-side. It was nothing short of a pleasant morning. 
#revelstoke #marmot #wereoutthere

Photos: @mason_mashon

From the mouth of the cave, we look up and scout a few potential lines to ski. We set our sights on a large ramp across the valley and opt for the most direct route as we‚Äôre running low on daylight. We switch-backed our way up a small climb and reached a very steep bootpack route. I‚Äôve done my share of bootpacking, but for a few reasons, this one was a bit spooky.

First, keeping up with Ruedi (our guide) is no easy task and not wanting to slow him down, I didn‚Äôt dare take any time to catch my breath. Second, the snow was very sugary and unstable. Meredith has even more experience than I do with this type of ski-mountaineering, and she was spooked, too. Every step felt like it might give. It didn‚Äôt help that Ruedi regularly gave blunt advice such as, ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt fall here or you‚Äôll slide down that cliff and die.‚Äù Although there were not many specific peaks on the agenda as the goal was to have no expectations, there was one line we wanted‚Ä¶ The Ramp. We didn‚Äôt get on the first try. Weather window wasn‚Äôt right. We took the opportunity to ski other incredible lines while allowing our thoughts to manifest about the Ramp. 
#marmot #bornwild #revelstoke #ski #bc 
Photos: @mason_mashon

And now.....we descend. The vastness and density of the Selkirk becomes more and more apparent. Truly stunning. Endless peaks in every direction. We ran a few laps in the area directly above the ladders, chasing the sections with the least sun exposure. Pure bliss.

#revelstoke #marmot #wereoutthere

"As expected, Ruedi is cracking the whip first thing in the morning. Eat your muesli quickly, slug some coffee, and get your sh** together. You do not want to feel Ruedi‚Äôs eyes on you if your behind schedule." The ladder was next.

#revelstoke #marmot #selkirkmountains #northcascades #pnw

"Striations of blue and white like a sandstone slot canyon unfold all around me. Light dashes in and bounces around the cathedral of ice. I‚Äôve seen images of ice caves and massive ice structures, but this experience epitomized the expression, ‚Äúphotos don‚Äôt do it justice‚Äù." The ice moves constantly. The glaciers let you in. Respect the beauty and the opportunity to be among the forces that are entirely more powerful than us. 
#icecave #wereoutthere #marmot #bornwild

Hut life in the backcountry is the time to regroup, eat well, have a beverage, dry your ski clothes above the wood burning stove, break out the maps to contemplate the next mountain objective and play highly competitive rounds of scrabble. ‚ÄúCook Dan‚Äù kept the room alive with satiable smells and contagious banter as the team was either on the verge of passing out from the day or obtaining a third wind. It's these moments where connecting with friends, family and those needing warmth are most important. Your family is anyone who you break bread with, adventure with and make the world a better place with. 
The stars above were limitless. The moon light kissed tomorrow slopes as they yearned for more soft turns. The ladder, although daunting, would be the next challenge faced. 
#revelstoke #marmot #wereouthere #hutlife #backcountryski @selkirkmtnexperience

Video: @newsatlascollective

From the mouth of the cave, we look up and scout a few potential lines to ski. "As expected, Ruedi is cracking the whip first thing in the morning. Eat your muesli quickly, slug some coffee, and get your sh** together. You do not want to feel Ruedi‚Äôs eyes on you if your behind schedule." The ladder was next.
